<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
    <!-- Deliberately empty. App Sandbox is NOT enabled: this build ships outside the Mac
         App Store under Developer ID, and Velopack self-update replaces the .app bundle,
         which the sandbox forbids. Every entitlement we previously set is sandbox-only and
         therefore inert without it, so they are removed rather than left as dead config.

         Restore all three if a sandboxed channel (e.g. Mac App Store) is ever added:

           com.apple.security.app-sandbox
           com.apple.security.network.client
               Required for outgoing connections once sandboxed.
           com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write
               Required for certificate import, and must be read-write even though the file
               is only ever read: MAUI's FilePicker builds UIDocumentPickerViewController
               with UIDocumentPickerMode.Open (open-in-place), so the system requests a
               read-write sandbox extension. With read-only the request is denied, the
               picker returns no URL, and PickAsync reports a cancel indistinguishable from
               the user backing out — import fails silently. -->
    <dict>
    </dict>
</plist>
